						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in front of the dilapidated Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva 1547 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1469, Plavaṅga, Bhādrapada śu. 12.</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1547 A.D., August 27, Saturday.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a gift by <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Rāmayadēva-Mahārāja and Yaṟaguḍi Tirumaladēva Mahārāja to the god Chennakēśava, who was worshipped by the <hi rend="italic">barber (Mangaḷa)</hi> community.</p>						

						</summary>
